<br>
DO UNTO OTHERS AS YOU WOULD HAVE THEM DO UNTO YOU!<br>
If you feel it will piss you off to have someone do it to you, don't even think about doing it to them! Keep the game clean!<br>
<br>
Guild chat should be rated PG 13. What is said in group is at groups discretion. There are people of all ages that will be part of our family and making someone feel uncomfortable due to language is just not a good thing. If you are even somewhat hesitant about hitting the return button after or during your typing, it is best to just delete what you were going to say.<br>
<br>
Please no guild bashing on any boards. This includes /ooc /shout /say or even in /group. If you need to, use our private areas. Everyone needs a place to rant. Send the guild leader or an officer a tell and whine all you want. Remember that one bad incident shouldn't focus blame on a whole guild. Give peace a chance!<br>
<br>
Guild invites are, by design, reserved for officers. Applicants will need to be sponsored by at least five (5) guild members. This will be discussed in the private forums. We have no level limit but folks from levels 1 to 30 must understand that there are not many in this guild at those levels. Events and raids for you will be at a minimum.<br>
<br>
No power looting or ninja looting. Everyone in your group deserves a fair share. Turn on split, take turns, whatever works best for everyone there. Some classes even deserve the cash drops more so due to reagent use. Clerics would be a priority here, with enchanters a close second in some locations.<br>
<br>
Group loot should be awarded to or rolled by the appropriate classes and people present that will use them first. Senior officer or group leader decides. Guild tag has no bearing on the loot distribution. The people in the group putting their life on the line get 100% recognition for their efforts, whether they are guildies or not. We aren't here to feed your twinks. If no one else wants something we may roll for twink drops.<br>
<br>
Most events will be run openly and posted on our boards. Due to the amount of people in our guild and in the Crusaders of Faith, our closest ally guild, keeping these events open to the public is, in many cases, the only way to ensure the numbers we need. In the case of needing more people than both guild can supply, the event will be posted on other guild sites. This will occur only after ample time has been given for KoI and CoF folks to sign up.<br>
<br>
Disputes need to be taken up with an officer. That includes internally or with other guilds. How you represent yourself to another guild reflect on everyone sharing your tag. No hotheads need apply unless you understand you need to let officers handle the conflicts that do arise.<br>
<br>
We are here to help the members of our family. We aren't here to chastise, ridicule, or embarrass our friends. If you feel the need to bash your guild members repeatedly just to feel better about yourself, please go elsewhere.<br>
<br>
Learn your class. To do things effectively in Norrath with a small bunch of people, talent is required. Learn your class, ask questions, practice, read boards, try new things. If you are interested in a guild that will power level you to 60 and get you items on Ebay you are on the wrong web page. It takes time to learn your class and have the opportunity to be faced with a wide variety of scenarios, especially when the crap hits the fan. There is nothing that can teach you THAT but time and experience.<br>
<br>
You are 100% accountable for anything your character does. Anything they do is a reflection on us as a whole. This includes shared accounts or the sharing of accounts. It happens and that's fine, but please remember that if they mess up and give you a bad name and therefore the guild, you are the one that faces those consequences.<br>
<br>
